The paper deals with optimization problems in matrix models, which are often encountered in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of static symmetry-breaking ordering constraints is a technique commonly used in constraint programming (cs.PL) and logic programming (cs.SE). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of graph-based representations to identify symmetries, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and combinatorics (cs.LO).
